sections.Trivia:
- It is the only manga-based case which only includes Takagi as the police in the crime scene.
- The real location is BritishPub&Bar The Cluriaune in Shinjuku.
- The suspects' names are related to "sports"[1]:
Teruaki Kunisue (国末 照明) comes from tennis (テニス ,tenisu?) ;
Kazuo Satsuma (薩摩 和雄) comes from football/soccer (サッカー ,sakkā?) ;
Kengo Harufuji (春藤 健吾) comes from golf (ゴルフ ,gorufu?) ;
Takuya Kyuma (久間 卓哉) comes from table tennis (卓球 ,takkyū?) and baseball (野球 ,yakyū?)
Additionally, the athletes' names come from real-life athletes. Kokuhō (黒鵬) comes from sumo wrestler Hakuhō (白鵬), Akashōryū (赤青龍) comes from sumo wrestler Asashōryū (朝青龍) and Sho Migikawa (右川 翔) comes from golfer Ryo Ishikawa (石川 遼).
